Overview

Audi Malaysia offers its flagship sedan, the 2015 A8 in a sole variant and long wheelbase guise. Priced at RM656, 900, it competes with other large limos like the Mercedes-Benz S-Class, Jaguar XJ, BMW 7-Series and Lexus LS.

The 2015 Audi A8L features a mechanically charged 3.0-litre petrol V6 and an eight-speed torque converter type automatic transmission combo. The direct injected V6 mill outputs 310hp from 5,200rpm to 6,500rpm and 440Nm of torque from 2,900rpm to 4,750rpm. Drive is sent to all four corners via the carmaker’s well known quattro all-wheel drive system. It is capable of accelerating from a standstill to 100km/h in 5.9 seconds before hitting an electronically limited top speed of 250km/h. Fuel consumption and CO2 emissions are rated at 7.9-litre/100km and 184g/km respectively.

In terms of kit, this German luxury sedan comes packed with a lot of them. Highlights include 19-inch polished cast aluminium wheels with 255/45 series tires, automatic Xenon head lamps, LED daytime running lights, a glass sunroof, parking aid plus with reverse camera, cruise control, rear seat entertainment, auto start/stop with energy recovery, adaptive air suspension, power-assist closing doors and an Audi Drive Select system with four modes – Auto, Comfort, Dynamic and Efficiency.

Infotainment system in the Audi A8 consists of a 14-speaker 600 watt audio system and an eight-inch colour that supports iPod, USB, DVD and Bluetooth.  Features such as leather wrapped multifunction steering wheel with paddle shifters, four-zone auto climate control, rain sensor, LED ambient lighting, electric blinds, Valcona leather covered electric front and rear seats are standard.

Safety wise, this large limo is equipped with eight airbags, electronic stabilization program, traction control, ABS with EBD and Brake Assist, electronic locking differential, ISOFIX anchor points and anti-theft wheel bolts. 
